<subSubSection box="[151,682,510,535]" pageId="43" pageNumber="244" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="43.[151,1437,510,1111]" box="[151,682,510,535]" pageId="43" pageNumber="244">This new species is named for the type locality.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="43" pageNumber="244" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="43.[151,1437,510,1111]" pageId="43" pageNumber="244">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,546,571]" pageId="43" pageNumber="244">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The female’s unique, mostly yellow vertex and genae separate this species from all the other Afrotropical 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ashmead" authorityYear="1899" box="[296,411,582,607]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="43" pageNumber="244" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Anthidiini">Anthidiini</taxonomicName>
in which these structures are largely black. (
<figureCitation box="[911,1035,582,607]" captionStart="FIGURE 35" captionStartId="44.[151,250,2004,2026]" captionTargetBox="[156,1399,351,1981]" captionTargetId="figure@44.[156,1416,351,1981]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURE 35.Anthidiellum somaliense. A–B FEMALE.A.HABItUS.B.FAcE.c–D.MALE.c. HABItUS." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1208860/files/figure.png" pageId="43" pageNumber="244">Fig. 35a–c</figureCitation>
). The male is unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="43" pageNumber="244" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="43.[151,1437,510,1111]" pageId="43" pageNumber="244">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,618,643]" pageId="43" pageNumber="244">Description.</emphasis>
Female. Integument of head and mesosoma black with pale yellow maculation on lower face (up to a little above antennal sockets), posterior vertex, most gena, mandible, anterodistal antennal scape, broad lateral scutum margin, axilla, posterior scutellum, mesepisternum below pronotal lobe, most mesepimeron, all legs, T1– T3 anterolaterally (blackish mesally, posterior margin orange), T4–T5 cross-bands (broad posterior margin orange), T6 (
<figureCitation box="[299,423,762,787]" captionStart="FIGURE 35" captionStartId="44.[151,250,2004,2026]" captionTargetBox="[156,1399,351,1981]" captionTargetId="figure@44.[156,1416,351,1981]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURE 35.Anthidiellum somaliense. A–B FEMALE.A.HABItUS.B.FAcE.c–D.MALE.c. HABItUS." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1208860/files/figure.png" pageId="43" pageNumber="244">Fig. 35a–c</figureCitation>
). Scopa white (
<figureCitation box="[598,695,762,787]" captionStart="FIGURE 35" captionStartId="44.[151,250,2004,2026]" captionTargetBox="[156,1399,351,1981]" captionTargetId="figure@44.[156,1416,351,1981]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURE 35.Anthidiellum somaliense. A–B FEMALE.A.HABItUS.B.FAcE.c–D.MALE.c. HABItUS." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1208860/files/figure.png" pageId="43" pageNumber="244">Fig. 35c</figureCitation>
). Lengths: face 
<quantity box="[876,966,763,787]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.2" pageId="43" pageNumber="244" unit="mm" value="4.2">4.2 mm</quantity>
; scutum 
<quantity box="[1067,1157,762,787]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="43" pageNumber="244" unit="mm" value="1.5">1.5 mm</quantity>
; forewing 4.0 mm; body 
<quantity box="[151,245,798,823]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.4" pageId="43" pageNumber="244" unit="mm" value="5.4">5.4 mm</quantity>
. Structure. Head. Epistomal suture flattish dorsolaterally (
<figureCitation box="[930,1017,798,823]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1315,1337]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,783,1290]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,782,1290]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Anthidiellum, FEMALE,FAcE SHOWINg SHAPE OF cLyPEUS.A.DIStINctLy ROUNDED ABOVE.B.SLIgHt ROUNDED ABOVE." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1208806/files/figure.png" pageId="43" pageNumber="244">Fig. 1b</figureCitation>
); lower epistomal suture projection adjacent to opposite inner antennal socket edge (
<figureCitation box="[707,790,834,859]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1315,1337]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,783,1290]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,782,1290]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Anthidiellum, FEMALE,FAcE SHOWINg SHAPE OF cLyPEUS.A.DIStINctLy ROUNDED ABOVE.B.SLIgHt ROUNDED ABOVE." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1208806/files/figure.png" pageId="43" pageNumber="244">Fig. 1b</figureCitation>
); preoccipital region rounded; scutum gently and evenly convex, punctate laterally; omaulus strongly carinate; fore and middle femora with squamose vestiture posteriorly; hind basitarsus wide (length 1.5x width); propodeum striate dorsolaterally, vertical surface mostly reticulate sculpture.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="43.[151,1437,510,1111]" box="[199,389,978,1003]" pageId="43" pageNumber="244">Male. Unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
